<description>Back scattering and asymmetry in crystals
________

This examples is used to test automatic calculation of the Bragg angle in crystals in backscattering geometry and highly asymmetric cut.

.. imagezoom:: _images/exp04_glow.png
   :scale: 60%

Notice that the asymmetry angle *alpha* is a property of the optical element, not the material.


.. imagezoom:: _images/exp04_p01.png
   :scale: 60%

Make sure that the asymmetry angle matches the orientation of the optical element.


.. imagezoom:: _images/exp04_p02.png
   :scale: 60%

Energy resolution should consequently improve.


.. imagezoom:: _images/exp04_p03.png
   :scale: 60%

In order to save the generated plot give it's *saveName* parameter a meaningful value.


.. imagezoom:: _images/exp04_p04.png
   :scale: 60%</description>
